    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0159">
<l>cuṭṭumuta lākiya vikara viṟutiyu</l>
<l>mekaramutal viṉāvi ṉikara viṟutiyuñ</l>
<l>cuṭṭucciṉai nīṭiya vaiye ṉiṟutiyum</l>
<l>yāveṉ viṉāvi ṉaiye ṉiṟutiyum</l>
<l>valleḻuttu mikunavu muṟaḻā kunavuñ</l>
<l>colliyaṉ maruṅki ṉuḷaveṉa moḻipa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>In non-case relationship,</l>
<l>the nouns which end in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-i</foreign> [or] <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ai</foreign></l>
<l>have three [possible] rules :</l>
<l>they are,</l>
<l>absence of any change, [obligatory] insertion of plosive,</l>
<l>and optional insertion of plosive ;</l>
<l>so say the scholars.<note place="foot">Illustrations:<foreign xml:lang="ta"> parutti|arai - kuṟitu (absence of change) ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">kiḷi kuṟitu &amp; kiḷikkuṟitu, tiṉa kuṟitu ~ tiṉaikkuṟitu</foreign> (optional insertion) ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">pulikkoṟṟaṉ</foreign> (obligatory insertion).</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
